	*** Callback
	    - When the server files are updated, the callback function will be
	      triggered to notify the client instead of letting the client to poll the
	      file status (/e.g.,/ =getstat()=)
	    - Implication: the server will need to keep a table to keep track of the
	      connected client
	    - the callback function *will not send the newer version of the file*; it
	      will only notify the client that such file is not valid anymore.
	      - =open()= will communicate with the server and only pull the file when
	        the local copy is not valid.
